74.5	Colonoscopy	Colonoscopy	Colonoscopy is the endoscopic examination of the large bowel and the distal part of the small bowel with a CCD camera or a fiber optic camera on a flexible tube passed through the anus. It may provide a visual diagnosis (e.g. ulceration, polyps) and grants the opportunity for biopsy or removal of suspected lesions.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ef/Endomucosal_resection_1.jpg/116px-Endomucosal_resection_1.jpg
